summary:
Hey again, y’all!
So, as many of you know, I suffer from a currently undiagnosed chronic pain condition.
During the passed year,...
body:
Robin’s Walker Fund!

Hey again, y’all!

So, as many of you know, I suffer from a currently undiagnosed chronic pain condition.

During the passed year, my chronic pain has gotten significantly worse, to the point where I have days where I physically cannot get out of bed, because I’m either in so much pain that moving even an inch hurts, or my legs can’t support my weight, and more often than not I require the support of my cane even on a good day.

This has been causing me to miss classes more than I would like, and not be able to leave my room very much, as well as not being able to stand for more than 15 minutes, even with my cane.

Because of this, and the fact that my cane cannot offer me enough support on bad days. I’m currently saving up to purchase a walker.

[Image Description: a screenshot from the website Ko-fi, labeled “Walker Fund,” and giving the same information listed above. So far it has reached 29% of a $200 goal. End Description]

I have my Ko-fi goal set to help pay for getting the walker. The goal is to save up $200, to cover the cost of the walker and the cost of shipping.

If you’re able to help out and you want to, I would super appreciate it! But you are by no means obligated to. I am saving up for the walker regardless, donations to my Ko-fi is just assisting me in getting the walker faster than I would otherwise, as all Ko-fi donations will be going towards the walker.

If you would rather commission me, and get a product in return for sending me money, that is absolutely an option.

The walker I’m saving up for is this one:

[Image Description: A screenshot from eBay of a bright red Drive brand rollator walker with a seat, as well as a bag to hold things. End Description]

The link to my Ko-fi is here!

My commission prices can be found here!

All donations will get a shoutout on my Instagram!
